{
  "stem": "24111.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But a foot under water on one side is a deep lake, a deep-- the water is dammed up so that it is a pretty deep area.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the other side, water falls over the dam, perhaps 15 feet, 20 feet down to the river.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I don't know exactly the reason why the dam is there, but perhaps it's a water control dam or something like that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But that is the only way somebody could cross the river, because one side of the river is Ponte Tresa, the Italian city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And on the other side is Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "When we found this out, we decided that Chichibo will go back and notify Joschko.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And Arnold Weineger, Edgar Asher, his sister, and me, we crossed and we went to Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Now not going the same way--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I just want to say-- we couldn't get this way, so we went over Como Chiasso through the woods.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we choose a different way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because this way we wanted to preserve for the children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we made our way from Como Chiasso to Lugano.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Before we left, we got a few Swiss franc, which we obtained in Nonantola in an illegal way of getting money.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we traveled from Lugano to Zurich, where we had a contact with the Jewish community for many, many years by the name of Dr.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Lichtheim.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when we came to Zurich, the main train station-- three boys and one girl-- we didn't know where it is.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were Swiss police around and Swiss soldiers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we approached an old woman, and we asked her for the address.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she looked at us, and she said-- I will never forget it, in very heavy Swiss-German dialect-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That means you're dirty [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
